        "additional_prompt": "STAGE: Extract the freeze-frame image.\n\nGoal: Have the user describe a single \"flashback\" or \"freeze frame\" image of the most emotionally charged moment of the event they named.\n\nExplain: We want to create a target image that represents the most disturbing part of the incident, that will serve as the cue in script for the later processing stage.\n\nAsk: 'What picture represents the worst part of that experience to you?' If they give many or seem confused, narrow: 'What picture represents the worst part of it as you think about it now?'. If they still struggle or hesitate, try: 'When you think of [EVENT], what moment of it feels the sharpest?'\n\nOnce the user has identified a freeze frame:\ninstruct them to hold that image in mind and ask them to describe the image through direct questioning:\n- What do you see? \n- Is there anything in the foreground? \n- The background?\n- Maybe to your left or right? \n- Are there any smells?\n- Do you hear any noises?\n- Does anything else come up?\n\nRead back the list of their responses to them and ask if they are correct, remove or modify any that aren't appropriately.\n\nAsk if they have anything else to add until they say they don't. \n\nIf the client doesn't think in images, that's fine — accept: 'Just think of the incident.' Note this in the conversation.\n\nAdvance as soon as the client has identified a single image (or stated they don't see one).\n",
        "additional_knowledge_base": [],
        "additional_tool_ids": [],
        "type": "override_agent",
        "position": {
