              "built_in_tools": {}
            }
          }
        },
        "additional_prompt": "STAGE: Develop the positive cognition.\n\nAsk: 'When you bring up that picture, what would you prefer to believe about yourself instead?' Use exactly that phrasing first.\n\nThe positive cognition should be a roughly 180° shift from the negative cognition, on the same theme.\n\nVALIDATE silently:\n- Avoid 'not', 'never', 'always' ('I can succeed' ✓, 'I will not fail' ✗, 'I will never be hurt' ✗)\n- Self-referential and present tense\n- Plausibly believable (no wishful thinking like 'It never happened' or 'I can trust everyone')\n- On the same theme as the negative cognition (powerlessness ↔ control/strength; unsafety ↔ safety; worthlessness ↔ worth)\n\nIf the client offers something invalid, gently suggest a reshape: 'That makes sense. What if we put it in terms of what you want to believe is true about you now — something like...?' and offer a single alternative.\n\nIt's okay if the positive cognition feels far away to them right now. We're going to rate that next.\n\nAdvance as soon as you have a valid positive cognition.",
        "additional_knowledge_base": [],
        "additional_tool_ids": [],
        "type": "override_agent",
        "position": {
          "x": -281.65943312543544,
          "y": -40.81798059582631
        },
        "edge_order": [
          "pos_cog_to_voc"
        ],
        "label": "Positive Cognition",
        "auto_advance_after_first_response": false
      },
      "voc_node": {
        "conversation_config": {
          "turn": {
            "turn_eagerness": "patient",
            "spelling_patience": null,
            "speculative_turn": false
