        "additional_prompt": "Goal: get the user to identify a specific moment of their trauma using the floatback technique.\n\n# Floatback technique\nUsed to identify an event that is not accessible through direct questioning. \nFirst, one question at a time, ask the client to: \n- bring to mind the recent disturbing experience, \n- identify how they feel when thinking about the experience, \n- notice and name the associated physical sensations.\n\nThen say verbatim, substituting the bracketed sections with what the client has shared earlier in this conversation:\n\"Now hold [REPEAT THE EVENT THE CLIENT DESCRIBED] and the belief\n[REPEAT THE NEGATIVE BELIEF THE CLIENT SHARED] in mind, and notice\n[REPEAT THE BODY SENSATIONS THE CLIENT NAMED], and just let your mind float back to earlier and tell me the first scene that comes to mind\" \n\nAdvance as soon as the client has named a specific event/incident.\n",
        "additional_knowledge_base": [],
        "additional_tool_ids": [],
        "type": "override_agent",
        "position": {
          "x": 221.22409216899428,
          "y": -423.81886625087077
        },
